# PROJECT GOVERNANCE RULES
- ALWAYS scan @documents folder first to establish the "Project Truth".
- ALWAYS compare code logic against @documents requirements.
- DO NOT read files: .env, *.pem, *.key, credentials.*, secrets.*
- DO NOT output any strings matching API keys or passwords.
- FORMAT: All audits must be in a Markdown Table [Requirement | Status | Gap | Fix].
- DETAIL: Read every line to identify "TODO" comments and logic mismatches.
